title.narrative: OUTPUT 3.1: IMPROVED Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) IN COMMUNITIES

description.narrative: Output 3.1: Children less than 5 years old and women have access to improved and sustainable water, sanitation and hygiene services in rural and urban communities, including emergency affected communities, which contributes to Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 3: By 2019, children and their caregivers using safe water, and practicing safe sanitation and hygiene in targeted underserved areas increased .

title.narrative: Output 3.1: Children less than 5 years old and women have access to improved and sustainable water, sanitation and hygiene servicesin rural and urban communities, including emergency affected communities

description.narrative: By October 2019, there was an increase of 9,940 additional persons that have accessed sustainable drinking water services through installation of manually drilled boreholes fitted with hand pumps. Additional 65,864 persons (against the annual target of 97,500, or 68% of the target) gained access to basic sanitation services. The same number of people have adopted the practice of hand washing with soap. The above results were registered in areas with high vulnerability for children in six hard to reach counties in south east and northwest Liberia and Montserrado county. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:26/12/2019
